'''Al Hujayl''' is a town in [[Iraq]]. It is located east of River [[Tigris]] and north east of [[Al-Shirqat]] on the western banks of the river. It was captured by [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] in the [[Northern_Iraq_offensive_(June_2014)|2014 Northern Iraq Offensive]] and was recaptured by the [[Iraq|Iraqi]] government forces during the [[Hawija offensive (2017)|Hawija offensive]] in September, 2017. 

