{{Use British English|date=June 2017}}
'''Auchenshoogle''' is a fictional [[Scotland|Scottish]] town, an amalgam of [[Dundee]] and [[Glasgow]], the setting (originally unnamed) of the [[comic strips]] ''[[Oor Wullie]]'' and ''[[The Broons]]'' in ''[[The Sunday Post]]''. The name was used infrequently in the early days of the comic strip, coming into more frequent use in the late 1990s.

The term has since become a generic Scottish small-town name, used for humour or as a dummy name in legal discussions<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.caledonia.org.uk/land/feudal2.htm |title=The Abolition of Feudal Tenure etc. (Scotland) Act 2000. A Practical Guide for Community Groups |website=www.caledonia.org.uk |accessdate=12 February 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303185602/http://www.caledonia.org.uk/land/feudal2.htm |archivedate=3 March 2016 |df= }}</ref> and is often claimed to be in [[Inverness-shire]].

