[[Image:Geografischer Mittelpunkt der Schweiz.JPG|thumb|Marker symbolizing the geographical centre of Switzerland]] [[Image:Stein und Tafel beim Mittelpunkt der Schweiz.jpg|thumb|Stone with the "Swiss of the Year" plaque at the centre of Switzerland]] The '''geographical centre of Switzerland''' has the coordinates {{coord|46|48|4|N|8|13|36|E|type:landmark_region:CH-OW_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}} ([[Swiss Grid]]: 660158/183641). It is located at Älggi-Alp in the municipality of [[Sachseln]], [[Obwalden]]. The point is the [[center of mass|centre of mass]] determined in 1988 by [[Swisstopo]].
As the point is difficult to access, a stone was set 500 m further south-east on Älggi Alp (1645 m). This symbolizes the centre of Switzerland and is located at {{coord|46|47|54|N|8|13|55|E|type:landmark_region:CH-OW_source:dewiki|name=Marker for the geographic centre of Switzerland}} (Swiss Grid: 660557/183338). A plaque on the stone commemorates the winner of the "[[Swiss of the Year]]" award.
