:''You may be looking for the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Nicosia, Sicily]]'' {{MOS|date=October 2015}}
The '''Latin ([[Roman Catholic]]) archbishopric of [[Nicosia]]''' was created during the [[Crusades|Crusades (1095-1487) in]] [[Cyprus]]; later becoming titular. According to the ''[[Catholic Encyclopedia]]''<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/11071c.htm CATHOLIC ENCYCLOPEDIA: Nicosia (Cyprus)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> 31 Latin archbishops served beginning in 1196, shortly after the conquest of Cyprus by [[Richard I of England]], to 1502.
==List (incomplete)== {{incomplete list|date=October 2015}} *Alan *Eustorgius, Eustorge de Montaigu,<ref>[http://www.allcrusades.com/CHRONOLOGICAL/chrono-1250-1299.html Chronological 1250–1299<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070403205733/http://www.allcrusades.com/CHRONOLOGICAL/chrono-1250-1299.html |date=2007-04-03 }}</ref> *[[Bartolommeo da Breganze]]<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/15404c.htm Catholic Encyclopedia: Vicenza<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> *1251–1261 [[Ugo di Fagiano]]<ref name="Catholic Encyclopedia: Cyprus">[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/04589a.htm Catholic Encyclopedia: Cyprus<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> *1274 [[Gérard de Langres]]<ref>[http://www.godrules.net/library/foxe/119foxe_b3.htm], [http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/04589a.htm]</ref> *1312-1332 [[Giovanni del Conte]] *1332-1342 [[Elias de Nabinal]]<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/04589a.htm],[http://users.bart.nl/~roestb/franciscan/franaute.htm]</ref> *1421 [[Hugues Lancelot de Lusignan|Hugh of Lusignan]]<ref>{{MLCC |warning=1 |url=http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/CYPRUS.htm |title-date= |title= CYPRUS<!-- Bot generated title -->|date=August 2012}}</ref> *1439 [[Galesius de Montolif]]<ref>[http://www.cambridge.org/ar/academic/subjects/history/regional-history-1500/history-cyprus-volume-1-1 A History of Cyprus<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> *1447 [[Andreas of Rhodes]]<ref name="Catholic Encyclopedia: Cyprus"/> *1456 [[James II of Cyprus]] *1495 [[Domenico Grimani]] *1559 [[Filippo Mocenigo]]<ref name="Catholic Encyclopedia: Cyprus"/> *1728 [[Raniero Felice Simonetti]]<ref>[http://www.fiu.edu/~mirandas/bios1747.htm The Cardinals of the Holy Roman Church - Biographical Dictionary - Consistory of April 10, 1747<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> *[[Carlo Vittorio Amedeo delle Lanze]]<ref>[http://www.fiu.edu/~mirandas/conclave-xviii.htm The Cardinals of the Holy Roman Church - Conclaves by century<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> *1818–1826 [[Antonio Fernando Echanove Zaldívar]]<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/tarr0.htm Metropolitan Archdiocese of Tarragona, Spain<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> *1915 [[Francesco Cherubini (archbishop)|Francesco Cherubini]]<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bcherub.html Archbishop Francesco Cherubini [Catholic-Hierarchy&#93;<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> *1934 [[Guglielmo Piani]]<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bpiani.html Archbishop Guglielmo Piani [Catholic-Hierarchy&#93;<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
