{{Infobox building | image = POL Warszawa Prosta Tower 01.jpg | location = [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]] | address = ul. Prosta 32 | start_date = 2007 | completion_date = 2011 | floor_area = 5350m² | floor_count = 19+5 | building_type = [[Office building]] | height = 70m | architecture_firm = Autorska Pracownia Architektury Kuryłowicz & Associates }}
{{Coord|52|13|52|N|20|59|17|E|display=title}}'''Prosta Tower''' is an office building located in [[Wola]], [[Warsaw]].
== History == [[File:Prosta Tower fasada.JPG|thumb|The building's facade.]] Building permits were obtained in 2006, and construction began in 2007 and ended in September 2011. Prosta Tower has 19 floors above ground and has a 5 floor car park underground. It adjoins the northern side of [[Łucka City]], which is a pairing system unique to Poland and is rarely seen elsewhere.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/934786231|title=Złota 44 i inne warszawskie niebotyki|last=).|first=Zieliński, Jarosław (1958-|date=2015|publisher=EKBIN Studio PR Ewa Kielak Ciemniewska|others=Szczawiński, Paweł., EKBIN Studio PR.|isbn=9788394094102|location=Warszawa|oclc=934786231}}</ref> The building was designed by [[Stefan Kuryłowicz]]. Initially, the project was a residential building, but the investor, [[Marvipol]], made it become an office building because of the [[Financial crisis of 2007–2008|financial crisis at the time]]. Because of this decision, the building gained its characteristic [[openwork]] [[facade]], which also limits sun exposure inside the building by around 40%.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.muratorplus.pl/inwestycje/inwestycje-komercyjne/biura-w-warszawie-biurowiec-prosta-tower-o-charakterystycznej-elewacji-z-betonowego-azuru_80345.html|title=Biura w Warszawie. Biurowiec Prosta Tower o charakterystycznej elewacji z betonowego ażuru|work=Muratorplus.pl|access-date=2017-08-15}}</ref>
